- GET /api/sessions/:id
- GET /api/sessions/:id/export?format=csv/json
- POST /api/sessions/:id/tag
- POST /api/sessions/:id/annotate
- POST /api/sessions/:id/resend-webhook
- POST /api/sessions/export (bulk)
- GET /api/dashboard/summary
- GET /api/dashboard/recent-sessions
- GET /api/dashboard/alerts
- POST /api/org/:orgId/webhooks
- GET /api/org/:orgId/settings
- PATCH /api/org/:orgId/settings
- POST /api/s3/presigned-upload
- GET /api/s3/presigned-download

Security
- Authentication: JWT/OAuth tokens; enforce org_id scoping.
- Authorization: RBAC for agents, admins; restrict export/purge to org admins or users with retention permissions.
- Data protection: redact sensitive respondent metadata where appropriate; implement audit trails for all destructive actions.
- Validation: Robust server-side validation for all inputs; validate shapes and required fields; use safe defaults for optional fields.

Validation
- Ensure all arrays are non-null before operations: (array ?? []).map(...); Array.isArray(array) ? array.map(...) : [].
- Use default empty objects/arrays in destructuring: const { items = [], count = 0 } = response ?? {}.
- Supabase-like patterns adapted: if using Supabase, follow data ?? [] patterns for results; otherwise implement equivalent guards.
- Use consistent error handling and return structured error responses with codes and user-friendly messages.

Acceptance Criteria
- [ ] Data is persisted with a normalized session schema, including transcript, structured fields, timestamps, metadata, and attachments.
- [ ] CSV and JSON exports stream correctly for large datasets, with progress reporting and completion notification.
- [ ] Pre-signed S3 upload/download flows work securely for avatars, PDFs, and transcripts; assets are retrievable with expiry-limited URLs.
- [ ] Settings & Preferences page correctly manages email preferences, webhooks, LLM defaults, storage, team settings, and retention policies; changes persist and validate properly.
- [ ] Session Viewer displays full transcripts, extracted fields, timestamps, respondent metadata, and supports export/resend/tag/annotate actions with proper guards against nulls.
- [ ] Dashboard shows accurate metrics, recent sessions, quick actions, and system alerts; all data reads are guarded for nulls.
- [ ] All forms have proper validation, error messaging, and accessible UI; keyboard navigation works and color contrast meets guidelines.

UI/UX Guidelines
Apply the project's design system:
- Adhere to color palette, typography, grid, spacing, and card design as specified.
- Use consistent card styles for Session Cards and Dashboard widgets.
- Ensure interactive elements have hover/focus states with accessible contrast.
- Maintain a clean, minimal aesthetic with strong typography hierarchy and predictable component behavior.
- Use radial overlay for focus in hero areas where applicable.

Visual Style
- Implement the specified color palette and typography system.
- Use card-based layouts with subtle shadows and rounded corners.
- Include data visualization components with the muted, precise aesthetic described (sparklines, simple charts).

Key Design Elements (Reiterated)
- Card Design: white cards, 10–12px radius, subtle borders or shadows, hover lift.
- Navigation: topbar and left rail with active state indicators; responsive behavior.
- Data Visualization: blue primary metrics, low-ink visuals, clean legends.
- Interactive Elements: primary, secondary, tertiary button styles; input focus rings; error states with clear messages.
- Micro-interactions: gentle motion, quick hover transitions.

Mandatory Coding Standards — Runtime Safety
- Supabase/DB-like patterns: data ?? [] for results; Array.isArray guards.
- React useState: initialize arrays/objects with proper defaults (e.g., useState<Type[]>([])).
- API responses: validate shapes; const list = Array.isArray(response?.data) ? response.data : [].
- Optional chaining: use obj?.property?.nested to access nested fields.
- Destructuring with defaults: const { items = [], count = 0 } = response ?? {}.

Project Context Integration
- Target feature: Session Persistence & Export within ConverseForms.
- Normalized session schema with raw messages, structured fields, timestamps, and metadata.
- Export service streaming and notification.
- Retention policies and data purge capability.
- AWS S3 object storage for assets and transcripts.
- Pages: Settings & Preferences (page_006), Session Viewer (page_011), Dashboard (page_012).

